snippet.textDisplay: To all those ridiculing Hard Kaur, try to understand the lyrics and the similarities between both the singer's life, the reason behind having this mashup is I guess due to the similar struggles in their life as singers and also in life in general. Both are portraying their love for music in the song. And another reason is I guess because both have that raw feeling in their voice which is hard to get in new generation singers due to voice modulation.

snippet.textDisplay: I usually surf the comment section while listening to a song & I spotted a number of people who is calling Hard Kaur's rap crappy, but has applauded other crappy/sappy bollywood songs & mainstream bengali movie songs. I think that speaks enough about their taste in music. Also, if u don't like rap, nobody is forcing u to listen to it, but at least don't post hurtful comments about an artist who has raised herself to this level. & there are many other versions of this song on YouTube without the rap, go listen to those. This is Coke Studio, it is all about fusion & the message.
